what you're missing is style. and with this kind of story you have to have style. <br>
right now the story is very to the point. you want to write it so we can see the action in technicolor and hear the noises as if we were there. <br>
don't say Max put on &quot;black-tie gambling clothes.&quot; say he gets duded up, or puts on a gorilla suit (just another term for a tuxedo) or even better he's wearing one of those flashy colorful suits that sparkle a lot. this isn't a classy guy. show us how cheesy and low class he can be while at the same time make him seem cool. <br>
i really think if you wrote this in first person it would be so much better. put us right in Max's shoes and in his head. <br>
and incidentally no one at a casino would sell you a gun. he'd have to get the gun somewhere else. i mean, someone who works at a casino might sell guns on the side, but they wouldn't be dumb enough to be selling guns inside a building that has hundreds of millions of dollars inside. <br>
<br>
anyway, just a few suggestions. you may not be interested in rewriting this but if you do give a little thought to how you can give it a little more punch. <br>
